Class ModelManager

    public class ModelManager
extends java.lang.Object

    A class that implements the Model interface and manages the bookings.

      A constructor that is meant to initialize the instance variables as a new array lists that will store a list of all rooms and a list of booked rooms.

      • removeRoom

        public RoomTransfer removeRoom​(java.lang.String roomId)
        Method removing a room from the list of rooms in the system. To prevent data-corruption, it checks if the room corresponding to the ID passed as an argument has any current or future bookings using the isBookingAllowed method, and if this is not the case - removes it from the list.
        Specified by:
        removeRoom in interface Model
        Parameters:
        roomId - the ID of the room to be removed
        Returns:
        true if room is removed successfully
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if room to be removed has any current or future bookings.

                                 int dailyPrice)
        Method used for editing a room already added to the system. Firstly, the room is received from the roomList and then the roomtype and number of beds variables are changed according to the values passed as arguments.

        nrBeds - The (new) number of beds in the room.
        Returns:
        true if editing succeeds
